CS 4518 Mobile and Ubiquitous Computing
PA4 Ski Tracker App

Names: Chloe Polit and Jess Keene

How are you using your sensors to intelligently react to the user's environment and "assist" the user
Software sensor:
- Current weather updates from API to let user know current temperature and conditions on the mountains
Hardware sensors:
- Location services for altitude/GPS
- Accelerometer to track speeds of run / if user is stationary


Any instructions that we should know on how to run/use your application.
Run on emulator in Android Studio
Click start run button to begin tracking a run, button appearance should change and
click end run button to end run
Refer to the tabs for any further explanation or instruction.

Any references/resources used. I highly doubt this section will be blank, since there is so much we didn't cover in this class!

Resources:
Referenced
GompeiFountainJumpApp and CityExplorerApp for proper implementation of multiple tabs/screens,
MVVM architecture, and utilization of buttons for our main functionality within the app.
The usage of the models package from CityExplorerApp was implemented within our own app.
Also referred to Lecture 17 for further explanation about multiple tabs.

